    "plan_content": "## Plan: `uv cache stats`\n\nHere's the full implementation plan — **8 file changes, zero new dependencies**.\n\n### Files to modify (6):\n\n1. **`crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs`** — Add `CacheStats = 1 << 28` to `PreviewFeature` enum, plus matching entries in `as_str()` and `FromStr`\n\n2. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant to `CacheCommand` + a `StatsArgs` struct (mirrors `SizeArgs` exactly with the same `--human / -H / --human-readable` flag)\n\n3. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — Add `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` and `mod cache_stats;`\n\n4. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — Add `CacheCommand::Stats` dispatch arm after the `Size` arm (line 1181)\n\n5. **`crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs`** — Add `cache_stats()` command helper and `with_filtered_cache_stats()` filter (for snapshot test normalization) to `TestContext`\n\n6. **`crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs`** — Add `mod cache_stats;` alongside `mod cache_size;`\n\n### Files to create (2):\n\n7. **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** — Core logic: iterate `CacheBucket::iter()` (10 buckets), measure each with `diskus::DiskUsage`, print a 20-char left-padded table, then `---` separator and `Total` row\n\n8. **`crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs`** — 3 integration tests (empty cache all-zeros, raw bytes with packages, human-readable with packages)\n\n### Key design decisions:\n- Reuses `CacheBucket::iter()` — the same 10 buckets `cache size` and `cache clean` use (`Python` excluded, consistent with existing code)\n- Per-bucket measurement uses `diskus::DiskUsage` (already a dependency via `cache_size.rs`) on each bucket path independently\n- `CacheBucket`'s `Display` impl provides versioned directory names (`wheels-v6`, `sdists-v9`, etc.)\n- `--human` / `-H` / `--human-readable` flags and `human_readable_bytes()` formatting identical to `uv cache size`\n- Gated behind new `PreviewFeature::CacheStats` (`--preview-features cache-stats`) with identical experimental warning",
